g/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:19:  operational_claim: \\\"In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\\\"\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:29:  baseline_definitions:\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:30:    P0: Canonical point baseline using passive leaky linear non-spiking single-compartment neurons matched to the same connectome slice and readout.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:31:    P1: Stronger reduced baseline using an effective-point or reduced-compartment model with explicit synaptic integration current or explicit delay structure.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:40:    - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:41:      statement: Survival against the stronger reduced baseline P1.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:56:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, with the intact-minus-baseline gap contrasted against the shuffled condition\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:57:    expected_relationship: The surface-wave model produces a small but reproducible shared-output departure relative to the matched baseline.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:60:      - same stimulus\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:75:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, then intact versus shuffled\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:79:      - same stimulus\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:96:    comparison: (surface_wave/intact - baseline/intact) versus (surface_wave/shuffled - baseline/shuffled)\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:101:      - matched baseline arm\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:105:  - id: m1_survives_stronger_baseline\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:106:    name: Survival against stronger reduced baseline P1\\nconfig/