or_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 6 operator\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:1:# Milestone 6 Operator Bundle Contract And Discretization Choice\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:3:This note freezes the operator-facing asset contract for Milestone 6 so later\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:6:Milestone 5 geometry bundles.\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:10:The processed manifest now carries `_operator_contract_version:\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:11:operator_bundle.v2` plus a per-root `operator_bundle` block. That block owns:\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:13:- the fine operator archive\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:14:- the coarse operator archive\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:15:- the transfer-operator archive\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:16:- the operator metadata sidecar\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:19:- a versioned `operator_assembly` config snapshot\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:23:- transfer-operator availability\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:27:- `fine_operator` points to\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:28:  `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:29:- `coarse_operator` points to\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:30:  `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:32:  summary used for preview / QA and for reconstructing the patch partition\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:38:### Graph-based surface operators\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:57:- convergence to a surface PDE is weaker than for a metric-aware mesh operator\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:59:### Mesh-based operators\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:66:- coarse operators derived from fine operators and transfer maps\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:73:- gives a principled path to Galerkin coarse operators\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:83:The default fine-surface discretization for Milestone 6 is:\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:94:The default coarse construction is:\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:96:- fine-to-coarse restriction by lumped-mass patch averaging\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:97:- coarse-to-fine prolongation by piecewise-constant patch injection\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:98:- coarse operator by Galerkin projection from the fine operator\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:100:This keeps the fine and coarse systems comparable in one inner product instead\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:103:More explicitly, the Milestone 6 bundle serializes:\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:107:- coarse patch mass `M_c = P^T M_f P`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:108:- coarse patch stiffness `K_c = P^T K_f P`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:111:- normalized coarse operator `A_c = M_c^{-1/2} K_c M_c^{-1/2}`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:113:That means coarse dynamics are derived from the same variational object as the\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:114:fine surface operator instead of from an unrelated patch-edge heuristic.\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:118:`meshing.operator_assembly` is the versioned user-facing config block that\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:119:drives fine-operator assembly. The current schema version is\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:120:`operator_assembly.v1`.\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:136:  defined by the serialized `tangent_u` / `tangent_v` frames.\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:148:Identity anisotropy is required to reproduce the isotropic operator within an\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:149:absolute operator tolerance of `1e-10`, and the tests enforce that bound.\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:165:- only the diagonal tangent-basis model is supported in `operator_assembly.v1`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:174:Fallback is allowed when the default operator cannot be serialized safely or has\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:177:- `surface_graph_uniform_laplacian`\\ndocs/operator_bundle_design.md:185:2. a build is intentionally limited to the Mile