scretizations and operators\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Workload split:** Math/physics-heavy  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Suggested lead:** Grant  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Implementation support:** Jack\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Goal\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nTurn neuron surfaces into simulation-ready numerical objects.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Build\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- adjacency structures  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- geodesic neighborhoods  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- graph or cotangent Laplacian  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- patch graph  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- local tangent frames  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- boundary masks  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- optional anisotropy tensors  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine-to-coarse transfer operators\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Agent implements:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- sparse matrix construction code  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- asset serialization  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- performance optimization  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- operator test harnesses  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- visualization of operator outputs on meshes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Agent researches and weighs options, chooses best, implements and documents all reasoning in a mark down file:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- choosing the correct discretization family  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- deciding whether to use graph-based or mesh-based operators  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- specifying stability-relevant properties  \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- defining what should 