{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"agent_message","text":"Plan for the implementation:\n\n1. Add a library-owned retinal bundle workflow module on top of `retinal_sampling` that:\n   - records deterministic frame archives\n   - exposes a load/replay helper\n   - carries a formal early-visual mapping block instead of script-local conventions\n\n2. Extend the retinal contract metadata so the bundle explicitly describes:\n   - the simulator-facing unit/channel layout\n   - the default identity mapping from sampled ommatidia to early-visual units\n   - normalization, aggregation, polarity, and channel semantics\n\n3. Add regression tests for:\n   - deterministic serialization and loading of a recorded retinal bundle\n   - stable repeated-input behavior\n   - a motion-onset case where the mapped early-visual values change only because the source changed, not because bundle structure drifted\n\n4. Run the requested verification, then stage and commit only the ticket-related changes."}}
